      "content": "There are several reasons why a powerful entity might keep essential workers in the dark about the ultimate goal of a massive shift. Keeping employees focused on the immediate, granular tasks prevents panic, maintaining operational efficiency while the larger strategy is executed. Furthermore, knowing the \"reset\" point could give employees undue influence or cause premature resistance to the planned changes. This secrecy is often a tactic used to ensure smooth implementation of a predetermined, significant event.",
